      "Answer\n\nUpon further reflection, consider `a = 1`, `b = 2`.\n\nAs computed earlier, `(a + b)^7 - a^7 - b^7 = 2058`, and `7^3 = 343` divides `2058` (`2058 = 6 * 343`), but `7^4 = 2401` does not.\n\nThis gives `(a + b)^7 - a^7 - b^7 = 2058 = 2 * 3 * 7^3`.\n\nWe need `(a + b)^7 - a^7 - b^7` to include `7^7`, but this is not the case here.\n\nHowever, note that in general, for `a тЙб b тЙб 1 mod 7`, we have that `ab(a + b)(a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓)┬▓ тЙб 1 * 2 * (1 + 1 + 1)┬▓ тЙб 18 тЙб 4 mod 7`. \n\nHmm, no zero.\n\nAlternatively, take `a = 2`, `b = 1`.\n\nSame as `a = 1`, `b = 2`.\n\nMaybe no solution exists with small numbers? \n\nBut let's think differently: for `a = 1`, `b = 7^k - 1`.\n\nBut perhaps this is too complex.\n\n### Final Solution\n\nActually, there is a solution in the literature: `a = 1`, `b = 2`.\n\nBut in Lean, we need `(a + b)^7 - a^7 - b^7 = 2058` to",
      "\nBut `b = 2` gives `4 + 2 + 1 = 7 тЙб 7 тЙв 0 mod 343`.\n\nThe multiplicative inverse of `2` mod `343` is `172`, because `2 ┬╖ 172 = 344 тЙб 1 mod 343`.  \n\nWe can try to solve `b┬▓ + b + 1 тЙб 0 mod 343`. \n\nLetтАЩs try `b = 8`:\n`64 + 8 + 1 = 73 тЙв 0 mod 7`.\n\n`b = 5`: `25 + 5 + 1 = 31 тЙв 0 mod 7`. \n\nAlternatively, perhaps not `a = 1`.\n\nWait, we need `a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓ тЙб 0 mod 343`. LetтАЩs try `a = 7`, `b = 7┬▓ - 7 = 42` (since `a тЙб b тЙб 0 mod 7`, but this will make `ab(a + b) тЙб 0 mod 7`).\n\nThis seems not to help.\n\nInstead, perhaps use `a тЙб 1`, `b тЙб 2 mod 7` and try higher multiples.  \n\nLet me try `a = 1`, then `b = 2 + 7k`. Then:\n`a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓ = 1 + b + b┬▓`. For `k = 1`, `b = 9`, as above, we get `1 + 9 + 81 = 91`. \n\n`k = 2`, `b = 16`: `1 + 16 + 256 = 273 = 7 ┬╖ 39`.\n\n`(a + b)^7 - aтБ╖ - bтБ╖ = 7 ┬╖ 1 ┬╖ 16 ┬╖ 17 ┬╖ 273┬▓ = 7 ┬╖ 272 ┬╖ 273┬▓`.  \nWe need this divisible by `7тБ╖`, i.e., `272 ┬╖ 273┬▓` divisible by `7тБ╢`.  \nBut `273 = 7 ┬╖ 39`, `272 = 16 ┬╖ 17`, so we have `7тБ╢ ┬╖ 16 ┬╖ 17 ┬╖ 39┬▓`, which is fine! Wait no:  \n\n`273┬▓ = 7┬▓ ┬╖ 39┬▓`, so `272 ┬╖ 273┬▓ = 16 ┬╖ 17 ┬╖ 7┬▓ ┬╖ 39┬▓`.  \n\nThus, `(a + b)^7 - aтБ╖ - bтБ╖ = 7 ┬╖ 1 ┬╖ 16 ┬╖ 17 ┬╖ 7┬▓ ┬╖ 39┬▓ = 7┬│ ┬╖ 16 ┬╖ 17 ┬╖ 39┬▓`.  \n\nWe need `7тБ╖`, so we need `16 ┬╖ 17 ┬╖ 39┬▓` divisible by `7тБ┤`, which it isnтАЩt. \n\nThis approach still isnтАЩt working.\n\nLetтАЩs try `a = 7`, `b = 7`. Then `ab(a + b)` divisible by `7`. Not good.\n\nAlternatively, recall that we need `ab(a + b)` not divisible by `7`, but `7ab(a + b)(a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓)┬▓` divisible by `7тБ╖`, i.e., `ab(a + b)(a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓)┬▓ тЙб 0 mod 7тБ╢`.\n\nSince `ab(a + b) тЙв 0 mod 7`, it must be that `(a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓)┬▓ тЙб 0 mod 7тБ╢`, i.e., `a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓ тЙб 0 mod 7┬│ = 343`.\n\nSuppose `a тЙб 1 mod 7`, `b тЙб 2 mod 7`. Then `a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓ тЙб 1 + 2 + 4 тЙб 7 тЙб 0 mod 7`.  \n\nLetтАЩs try `a = 1`, `b = 2 + 7k`. \n\nWe need `a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓ тЙб 0 mod 343`:\n\\[\n1 + (2 + 7k) + (2 + 7k)^2 тЙб 0 mod 343\n\\]\nCompute for `k = 1`:\n`1 + 9 + 81 = 91 тЙб 91 тЙв 0`.  \n\n`k = 2`: `1 + 16 + 256 = 273 тЙб 273 тЙв 0`.\n\n`k = 3`: `1 + 23 + 529 = 553 тЙб 553 - 343 = 210 тЙв 0`.\n\n`k = 4`: `1 + 30 + 900 = 931 тЙб 931 - 2 ┬╖ 343 = 245 тЙв 0`.\n\n`k = 5`: `1 + 37 + 1369 = 1407 тЙб 1407 - 4 ┬╖ 343 = 1407 - 1372 = 35 тЙб 35 тЙв 0`.\n\n`k = 6`: `1 + 44 + 1936 = 1981 тЙб 1981 - 5 ┬╖ 343 = 1981 - 1715 = 266 тЙб 266 тЙв 0`.\n\nHmm, no luck. \n\nBut maybe `a тЙб 1`, `b тЙб 4 mod 7`. Then:\n`a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓ тЙб 1 + 4 + 16 тЙб 21 тЙб 0 mod 7`.\n\nTry `a = 1`, `b = 4`:\n`1 + 4 + 16 = 21 тЙб 0 mod 7`, but `ab(a + b) = 1 ┬╖ 4 ┬╖ 5 = 20 тЙб 6 тЙв 0 mod 7`.\n\nNow, `(a + b)^7 - aтБ╖ - bтБ╖ = 7ab(a + b)(a┬▓ + ab + b┬▓)┬▓ = 7 ┬╖ 20 ┬╖ 21┬▓ = 7 ┬╖ 20 ┬╖ 441 = 7 ┬╖ 20 ┬╖ 49 ┬╖ 9 = 7┬▓ ┬╖ 20 ┬╖ 49 ┬╖ 9`.\n\nWe need this to be divisible by `7тБ╖`, i.e., `20 ┬╖ 49 ┬╖ 9` divisible by `7тБ╡`. But `49 = 7┬▓`, so we have `7┬▓ ┬╖ 20 ┬╖ 9`, and need `7тБ╡`, so no.\n\nNot good. \n\nLetтАЩs try a different approach. \n\nTake `a = 1`, `b = 7┬▓ - 1 = 48`.  \n\nThen `a + b = 49`, and `ab(a + b) = 1 ┬╖ 48 ┬╖ 49 = 48 ┬╖ 49`, which is divisible by `7`. So no.\n\nAlternatively",
