\((a+b)^7 - a^7 - b^7 = 7ab(a+b)(a^2 + ab + b^2)^2\\). We need this to be divisible by \\(7^7\\), so we need \\(ab(a+b)(a^2 + ab + b^2)^2\\) to be divisible by \\(7^6\\).\n    \n    LetтАЩs choose \\(a\\) and \\(b\\) such that \\(a \\equiv 1 \\mod 7\\) and \\(b \\equiv 6 \\mod 7\\). Then:\n    - \\(a + b \\equiv 0 \\mod 7\\)\n    - \\(ab \\equiv 6 \\mod 7\\)\n    - \\(a^2 + ab + b^2 \\equiv 1 + 6 + 1 \\equiv 8 \\equiv 1 \\mod 7\\)\n    \n    But \\((a+b)^7 - a^7 - b^7 = 7ab(a+b)(a^2 + ab + b^2)^2\\). For this to be divisible by \\(7^7\\), since \\(a + b\\) is divisible by 7, we need the product to have at least \\(7^7\\). However, \\(ab \\equiv 6 \\mod 7\\) and \\((a^2 + ab + b^2)^2 \\equiv 1 \\mod 7\\), so the product would be divisible by \\(7 \\cdot 7^2 = 7^3\\), which is insufficient.\n    \n    Hmm, perhaps we need another approach. Let's try setting \\(a = 1\\) and see if there's a suitable \\(b\\).\n    \n    Let \\(a = 1\\) and try to find \\(b\\) such that:\n    - \\(1 \\cdot b \\cdot (1 + b)\\) is not divisible by 7.\n    - \\((1 + b)^7 - 1 - b^7\\) is divisible by \\(7^7\\).\n    \n    Let's calculate \\((1 + b)^7 - 1 - b^7\\):\n    \\[\n    (1 + b)^7 = 1 + 7b + 21b^2 + 35b^3 + 35b^4 + 21b^5 + 7b^6 + b^7\n    \\]\n    So:\n    \\[\n    (1 + b)^7 - 1 - b^7 = 7b + 21b^2 + 35b^3 + 35b^4 + 21b^5 + 7b^6 = 7b(1 + 3b + 5b^2 + 5b^3 + 3b^4 + b^5)\n    \\]\n    We need this to be divisible by \\(7^7\\), i.e.:\n    \\[\n    7b(1 + 3b + 5b^2 + 5b^3 + 3b^4 + b^5) \\equiv 0 \\mod 7^7\n    \\]\n    So we need \\(b(1 + 3b + 5b^2 + 5b^3 + 3b^4 + b^5)\\) to be divisible by \\(7^6\\).\n    \n    Let's try \\(b = 7^6\\):\n    \\[\n    b(1 + 3b + 5b^2 + 5b^3 + 3b^4 + b^5) = 7^6 (1 + 3 \\cdot 7^6 + 5 \\cdot 7^{12} + \\cdots) \\equiv 7^6 \\cdot 1 \\mod 7^7\n    \\]\n    But this is not divisible by \\(7^7\\).\n    \n    Try \\(b = 7^6 - 1\\):\n    - Not immediately helpful.\n    \n    Let's instead try to find \\(a = b\\) such that \\(2a^3\\) is not divisible by 7 and \\(2a^7\\